2026-04-20 | Count Derangements

Question
Return number of derangements of n elements.
	Key Insight
Recurrence relation:
		D(n) = (n - 1) × (D(n-1) + D(n-2))
Why?
- First element can go to (n-1) positions  
- Then two cases form → leads to recurrence  
	Base Cases
		D(1) = 0  
		D(2) = 1  
	Approach
1.	Use DP with two variables  
2.	Iterate from 3 to n  
3.	Apply recurrence  
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int countDerangements(int n) {
        if(n == 1) return 0;
        if(n == 2) return 1;
        int prev2 = 0; // D(1)
        int prev1 = 1; // D(2)
        for(int i = 3; i <= n; i++){
            int curr = (i - 1) * (prev1 + prev2);
            prev2 = prev1;
            prev1 = curr;
        }
        return prev1;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Derangements follow a **classic combinatorial DP pattern**.  
The recurrence:
		D(n) = (n-1)(D(n-1) + D(n-2))  
helps reduce exponential permutations into linear computation.
